50|$|When <b>forward</b> <b>biased,</b> a Schottky diode's {{voltage drop}} {{is much less}} than a {{standard}} silicon diode's, 0.25 V versus 0.6 V. In a standard saturated transistor, the base-to-collector voltage is 0.6 V. In a Schottky transistor, the Schottky diode shunts current from the base into the collector before the transistor goes into saturation.|$|E
