40|$|Using {{a market}} {{microstructure}} analytical framework we decompose the FX <b>forward</b> discount <b>bias</b> into elements due to time-varying risk premia (related to EBS order flow) and forecast errors derived using the Reuters survey of FX market participants. We find that both elements are significant {{contributors to the}} <b>forward</b> <b>bias</b> with risk premia being particularly important in currency pairs traditionally associated with carry trade activity. Part of order flow is driven by carry trade, and from our decomposition the carry trade driven risk premia account for about 50 % of the <b>forward</b> <b>bias.</b> Carry Trade; <b>Forward</b> Discount Puzzle; FX Microstructure; Survey Data...|$|R
